  "market_context": "The case covers the trading day following a prior session where Asia and London session highs/lows were established. Analyst marks previous day high/low and session levels as key liquidity zones before observing price action from Asia open through NY session.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept Asia low and London low without displacement, then formed displacement upward, tagged a 5-minute FVG, and ultimately expanded to sweep the previous day high as the final liquidity target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst marked previous day high and low on the chart as primary liquidity reference points for the next day.",
    "Step 2: Observed Asia session range formation and noted that Asia low was taken (swept) early in the session.",
    "Step 3: Watched London session develop and confirmed London low was also swept, with no significant displacement below it.",
    "Step 4: Identified initial upward displacement and a 5-minute fair value gap that subsequently got tagged.",
    "Step 5: Noted price targeting session highs (London session high) and then, after sweeping those, continued upward to take out the previous day high with displacement."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Previous day high/low and intraday session levels (Asia, London) form a hierarchy of liquidity targets. Price typically sweeps lower-tier liquidity first (session lows), then progresses to higher-tier targets (previous day high) after establishing structural break.",
